   ],
   "source": [
    "x1 = np.linspace(0,1,N+1)\n",
    "print np.trapz(f(x1),x1)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "collapsed": true
   },
   "source": [
    "Pros:\n",
    "* One can pass any kind of y,x input to be integrated, not only a function\n",
    "\n",
    "Cons:\n",
    "* Need to manually generate a list of x values every time"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Combining things\n",
    "But of course, one can also define:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 11,
   "metadata": {
    "collapsed": true
   },
